title: Spectroscopy of the 70,72Ge isotopes and structure of low-lying states of the 70,72,74,76Ge isotopes by (p,p`) inelastic scattering at 22 MeV.

x4freetext: Spectroscopy of the 70,72Ge isotopes and structure of
low-lying states of the 70,72,74,76Ge isotopes by
(p,p`) inelastic scattering at 22 MeV.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.453, p.389 (1986)
Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.385, p.430 (1982)

x4freetext: The outgoing particles were detected along the
focal plane of the split-pole magnetic spectrograph
using four position-sensitive silicon detectors of 2 mm
active thickness.
The targets were metallic self-supporting foils of
100 mu-g/cm2 enriched up to 96.2% and 98.2% in 70Ge
and 72Ge respectively, and 98.8% in 74Ge.
A mylar foil of appropriate thickness was set
before detectors to stop the protons. Particle
identification was obtained from the energy loss in the
detectors.
The relative normalization of the angular distributions
were derived from the counting of a Si(Li) monitor
detector set at 106 degr. This monitor was protected
from neutrons of the 12C(p,n) reaction on the Faraday
cup by a 200 mm bar of brass. The absolute cross
sections were obtained from comparison at 30 degrees
between the experimental data and the calculated
elastic cross section and were believed to be accurate
within 15%.
